5/5 these three trails combined are known as the #thruhikers Triple Crown 👑 👑 👑, a hiker who has thru hiked from end to end each of these three trails has earned their triple crown.

4/5 the third & youngest long trail in the US is the Continental Divide Trail or CDT. The CDT is by far the longest and most remote clocking in at 3100 miles from Mexico to Canada passing through NM, CO, WY, & MT. The trail is still unfinished in parts and offers multiple routes

3/5 the second is the Pacific Crest Trail or the PCT. The PCT is 2650 miles long from the Mexico/US border to the Canada/US border. It passes through CA, OR, & WA. From desert to rainforest with total elevation gain equal to summiting Mt. Everest from sea lvl more than 17 times.

2/5 the first of which and oldest, is the Appalachian Trail, know in the #thruhiking community as “the AT”. The AT runs 2190 miles from Georgia to Maine. Thru hikers walk across 14 states on their journey: GA, NC, TN, VA, WV, MD, PA, NJ, NY, CT, MA, VT, NH, ME.

1/5 thru hiking is the self supported pursuit of backpacking a trail system from end to end in one long extended trip, sometimes requiring several months to complete. There are hundreds of trails to choose from but in the U.S.A. 3 reign supreme.
